Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and slice @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites from greens.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wash out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until just softened, ~{1%minute}. Add @flour{1%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}. Whisk in @milk{6.75%ounce} and ⅓ cup pasta cooking water, breaking up any flour clumps. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir @cream cheese{2%tbsp} into pan with sauce until melted. Stir in mushrooms, cavatappi, and @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

> If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and scallion greens. Serve.